   "source": [
    "import cv2"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Take a video. 0 means the camera of my computer"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cap = cv2.VideoCapture(0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Get the Width and Height of the Video Frame"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "width = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FRAME_WIDTH))\n",
    "height = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FRAME_HEIGHT))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Get the Writer with the Video name, format, FPS, Width &Height\n",
    "\n",
    "##### For Windows        --> *'DIVX'\n",
    "##### For Linux or MacOS --> *'XVID'"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "output = cv2.VideoWriter(\"myvideo.mkv\", cv2.VideoWriter_fourcc(*'DIVX'), 20, (width, height))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Get ready to do Magic!"
   ]
  },
